ParameterInfo.description: A list of structures containing information to claim an assignment.

Operation.description: This operation claims assignments by deleting the resource pool assignments and assinging them to the logged in user. An assignment can be claimed only if the ScheduleTask object is assigned to any member in the ResourcePool object and the logged in user is a member of the ResourcePool object.
Operation.name: claimAssignments
Operation.returnDescription:
The ServiceData containing ResourceAssignment objects affected by the claim Assignments operation in the Created and Deleted list and the affected ScheduleTask objects in the Updated list.

The following partial errors may be returned:

230002 : One or more parameters passed to the function were invalid. See system log for details.
230045: The user does not have the correct access privileges to modify one or more objects.
230155: Task Assignments can only be claimed when the user claiming the Schedule Task is a member of the Resource Pool.

ParameterInfo.description: A list of structures containing information to create master Schedule objects.
True to perform the operation in background mode in a separate asynchronous server session. False to perform the operation synchronously.

Operation.description: This operation creates new master Schedule and inserts one or more Schedule objects specified in the input,into a master Schedule. The information needed to create the master Schedule is specified in the MasterScheduleCreateInput structure. In case of background mode,this operation files an asynchronous request to create master Schedule and releases the client immediately so that the user can perform other operation.
Operation.name: createMasterSchedule
Operation.returnDescription:
The newly created Schedule is added to the created list of the ServiceData. The following partial errors may be returned:-
    • 329011 : if the schedules to insert are not published.
    • 329012 : if the schedules to insert are template.
    • 329013 : when the user does not have the coordinator access on the schedules to insert.
    • 329014 : if the value of the "SM_LIMIT_SINGLE_MASTER_SCHED" preference is set to true.

ParameterInfo.description: Information about the Schedule to be loaded and the reference ScheduleTask from which to load the subsequent ScheduleTask objects.

Operation.description: Loads the ScheduleTask objects of a given Schedule based on the reference ScheduleTask. The number of ScheduleTask objects to be loaded will be determined by AWC_DefaultPageSize preference or ‘50’, if the preference is not found. This operation also loads all the Fnd0ProxyTask objects and TaskDependency relations which are referencing the loaded ScheduleTask objects.
Operation.name: loadSchedule
Operation.returnDescription:
The response containing the list of loaded ScheduleTask objects and its parents, Fnd0ProxyTask objects and TaskDependency objects. If the referenceTask in the input loadScheduleInfo is a schedule summary task, the response will also return the day ranges and the event ranges. Otherwise the day ranges and event ranges will be empty. The following partial errors may be returned:
    • 230061: The schedule has been deleted and cannot be accessed.
    • 230041: Getting tasks in schedule failed. See system log for details.
    • 230049: You do not have the latest schedule. Refresh the schedule to obtain the latest copy.
    • 230051: Failed to Check-Out a Schedule Manager application license.
    • 301003: The schedule uid to load is invalid. Please see the server error log file for details.

ParameterInfo.description: Information about the Schedule to be loaded and the reference ScheduleTask from which to load the subsequent ScheduleTask objects.

Operation.description: Loads the ScheduleTask objects of a given Schedule based on the reference ScheduleTask. The number of ScheduleTask objects to be loaded will be determined by AWC_DefaultPageSize preference or ‘50’, if the preference is not found. This operation also loads the baseline tasks, Fnd0ProxyTask objects and TaskDependency relations which are referencing the loaded ScheduleTask objects.
Operation.name: loadSchedule2
Operation.returnDescription:
The response containing the list of loaded ScheduleTask objects and its parents, baseline ScheduleTask objects, Fnd0ProxyTask objects and TaskDependency objects.
The taskBaselineMap structure in the response will be populated with start and finish dates of the baseline tasks, if the loadOptions structure in the loadScheduleInfo contains the key-value as 'baselineUid=UID of the baseline'. In addition, if the loadOptions contains 'loadBaselineTasks=true', the baseline tasks will also be returned.
The calendarInfo structure in the response will be populated if the loadOptions structure in the loadScheduleInfo contains the key-value as 'loadCalendarInfo=true'.

The following partial errors may be returned:
    • 230061: The schedule has been deleted and cannot be accessed.
    • 230041: Getting tasks in schedule failed. See system log for details.
    • 230049: You do not have the latest schedule. Refresh the schedule to obtain the latest copy.
    • 230051: Failed to Check-Out a Schedule Manager application license.
    • 301003: The schedule uid to load is invalid. Please see the server error log file for details.

ParameterInfo.description: Contains information about the type of operation to be performed and the configuration to be used.

Operation.description: Manages a ProgramView object based on the information provided in the ProgramViewInfo. This operation can create, configure and save a ProgramView object. The ProgramView configuration contains the list of Schedule UIDs, filters and groups.

The response containing the ScheduleTask objects loaded from the ProgramView and the day and event ranges of the owning Schedules. Partial errors are returned in the ServiceData:
    •    515024: The input object is not a valid Program View.
    •    329025: The Program View configuration is not valid.
    •    329026: The filter type is not valid.
    •    329027: The filter property is not valid.
    •    329028: The filter condition is not valid.
    •    329029: The group type is not valid.
    •    329030: The group property is not valid.
    •    329031: The Schedule UID is not valid.

ParameterInfo.description: A list of ScheduleMember objects to remove member assignments.
If true perform the operation in background mode in a separate asynchronous server session. False to perform the operation synchronously.

Operation.description: This operation removes all assignments of a ScheduleMember. The system will not delete the ScheduleMember object.
Operation.name: removeAssignments
Operation.returnDescription:
The ServiceData containing ResourceAssignment objects deleted by the operation in the Deleted list. The list will be empty in case of asynchronous mode. In Asynchronous mode, an Fnd0Message instance will be created for the success or failure. Errors will be stored in the Fnd0Message instance which can be queried for and accessed by the invoker of the operation. The Fnd0Message objects will not be returned by the operation

The following partial errors may be returned:
230045 : The user does not have the correct access privileges to modify one or more objects.
230061 : The Schedule has been deleted and cannot be accessed.
230091 : The task has been deleted and cannot be accessed.
230144 : Resource assignments cannot be added to or removed from the tasks because the workflow has already been triggered. Only the resource load of the existing assignment can be changed.
230107 : Cannot unassign a user who is assigned to a completed task.
230115 : The schedule cannot be updated because the system is configured to not allow the update of schedules when in the in_progress, complete, closed, aborted state. The preference “SM_PREVENT_UPDATE_STATES” specificies those states of the schedule cannot be updated.

Operation.name: removeAssignmentsAsync
Operation.returnDescription: There are no specific business errors returned.

ParameterInfo.description: A list of structures containing information to replace member assignments.
If true perform the operation in background mode in a separate asynchronous server session. False to perform the operation synchronously.

Operation.description: This operation removes all assignments of a ScheduleMember and assigns them to a new ScheduleMember. While replacing the assignments, the system will check if the new resource is a ScheduleMember. If not, the system will create a ScheduleMember for the resource and replace the assignments.
Operation.name: replaceMemberAssignments
Operation.returnDescription:
The ServiceData containing ResourceAssignment objects affected by the operation in the Updated list and the newly created ScheduleMember objects in the Created list. The list will be empty in case of asynchronous mode.

The following partial errors may be returned:

230002 : One or more parameters passed to the function were invalid. See system log for details.
230045 : You do not have the correct access privileges to modify one or more objects.
230061 : The Schedule has been deleted and cannot be accessed.
230091 : The task has been deleted and cannot be accessed.
230115 : The schedule cannot be updated because the system is configured to not allow the update of schedules when in the in_progress, complete, closed, or aborted state. The preference "SM_PREVENT_UPDATE_STATES" specificies those states of the schedule cannot be updated.
230144 : Resource assignments cannot be added to or removed from the tasks , because the workflow has already been triggered. Only the resource load of the existing assignment can be changed.
230162 : The Schedule Task cannot be updated, because it is in the in_progress, complete, closed, or aborted state. The preference "SM_PREVENT_TASK_START_UPDATE_STATES" specifies the states in which Schedule Tasks cannot be updated.

ParameterInfo.description: The Schedule that members and disciplines are part of.
The Discipline that will be assigned too all ScheduleMember assignments.
The discipline User.
If true, revert all assignments from ScheduleMember to Discipline, otherwise assign the Discipline to all the ScheduleMember assignments.
If true, performs the operation in background mode in a separate asynchronous server session. False performs the operation synchronously.

Operation.description:
This operation removes all assignments in a schedule of a Discipline and assigns them to the specified User. While designating the discipline, the system will check if the user is a ScheduleMember. If not, the system will create a ScheduleMember for the user.
The system will get and delete all resources assignments for the discipline in the schedule and create new resource assignments for the user.
The revert option is to revert the ResourceAssignment objects from the User to Discipline object for all schedule tasks in the schedule.
Operation.name: designateDiscipline
Operation.returnDescription:
The ServiceData containing ResourceAssignment objects affected by the operation in the Created and Deleted list and the affected ScheduleTask objects in the Updated list. The list will be empty in case of asynchronous mode.

The following partial errors may be returned:
230065: Resource assignments cannot be added, updated or deleted, and privileged user cannot be changed since the workflow process has been triggered at another site.
230045: The user does not have the correct access privileges to modify one or more objects.
230061: The schedule has been deleted and cannot be accessed.

ParameterInfo.description: The Schedule that members and disciplines are part of.
The Discipline that will be assigned too all ScheduleMember assignments.
The discipline User.
If true, revert all assignments from ScheduleMember to Discipline, otherwise assign the Discipline to all the ScheduleMember assignments.

Operation.description:
This operation removes all assignments in a schedule of a Discipline and assigns them to the specified User. While designating the discipline, the system will check if the user is a ScheduleMember. If not, the system will create a ScheduleMember for the user.
The system will get and delete all resources assignments for the discipline in the Schedule and create new resource assignments for the user.
The revert option is to revert the ResourceAssignment objects from the User to Discipline object for all schedule tasks in the Schedule.
Operation.name: designateDisciplineAsync
Operation.returnDescription: There are no specific business errors returned.

ParameterInfo.description: A list of UID of resources to load the resource chart information.
A list of Schedule or ScheduleTask objects assigned with resources. If the resources are not provided, the resources assigned to assingedObjects will be used to fetch the resource chart information.
The start date of the resource chart. If the date is not valid, the current date will be used.
The end date of the resource chart. If the date is not valid, a date that is two weeks from the start date will be used.
A list of Schedule objects to be used for calculation of resource chart information. If not provided, all the Schedule objects in the system will be used.

Specifies the options for loading resource chart.
Valid values are:
loadAssignedTasks : true/false (Set true for returning the assigned ScheduleTask objects in the ServiceData plain objects list; otherwise, not.)

Operation.description: The operation returns the resource chart information for the given resources assigned to the context objects. The resource load will be calculated for the date range between the given start and finish dates. The schedulesToInclude specifies the list of Schedule objects to be considered for calculating the resource chart information.
Operation.name: getResourceChartInfo
Operation.returnDescription:
The resource chart information for all the given resources. The resource chart information contains the capacity, availably, load and assigned ScheduleTask objects for the resources in the given date range.
If the user does not have sufficient privilege, or if the input parameters are invalid, the errors are returned in the ServiceData.

Following partial errors may be retuned:
• 230045 You do not have the correct access privileges to modify one or more objects
• 329025 The assigned object is not an instance of Schedule or ScheduleTask.
• 329026 The given resource UID is not valid.

ParameterInfo.description: A list of structures containing information to fetch the ScheduleTask objects assigned to the logged in User.

Operation.description: Loads the ScheduleTask objects assigned to the logged in user based on the information provided in the     ‘LoadAssignedTasksInfo’ inputs. The assigned tasks are determined by the ResourceAssigment relation where the primary object is ScheduleTask and the secondary is the current logged in User.
Operation.name: loadAssignedTasks
Operation.returnDescription:
The response containing the list of loaded assigned tasks information. The ServiceData will contain the plain objects populated with the loaded assigned tasks and it will hold the partial errors in case of operation failure.
The following partial errors may be returned:

•    515001: The access is denied.
•    515111: The instance is not loaded.

The following partial errors may be returned:

    • 329018: The schedule baseline to load is invalid.

OperationTemplate.description:
This operation removes all assignments in a schedule of a Discipline and assigns them to the specified User. While designating the discipline, the system will check if the user is a ScheduleMember. If not, the system will create a ScheduleMember for the user.
The system will get and delete all resources assignments for the discipline in the schedule and create new resource assignments for the user.
The revert option is to revert the ResourceAssignment objects from the User to Discipline object for all schedule tasks in the schedule.

The ServiceData containing ResourceAssignment objects affected by the operation in the Created and Deleted list and the affected ScheduleTask objects in the Updated list. The list will be empty in case of asynchronous mode.

The following partial errors may be returned:
230065: Resource assignments cannot be added, updated or deleted, and privileged user cannot be changed since the workflow process has been triggered at another site.
230045: The user does not have the correct access privileges to modify one or more objects.
230061: The schedule has been deleted and cannot be accessed.

StructElement.description: An array of ranges for the event day.
StructElement.name: ranges

Struct.description: Maps the weekdays to their ranges. The valid values for the days are 0 to 6 which represents Sunday through Saturday in the respective order. A range is a pair of start and end time of working hours. A day can have multiple ranges with breaks in-between in a working day.
Struct.name: DayRanges3

StructElement.description: The event date.
StructElement.name: eventDate

StructElement.description: An array of ranges for the event date. The number of ranges must be an even number as a range is represented as a pair of start and end time of working hours. A range must be represented in ‘hh:mm’ format, where ‘hh’ represents hours and ‘mm’ represents minutes. For example, the array [08:30, 12:30, 13:45, 16:45] represents two ranges. The first range has start time of 08:30 hours and end time of 12:30 hours. The second range has start time of 13:45 hours and end time of 16:45 hours.
StructElement.name: ranges

Struct.description: Maps an event date with its ranges. The number of ranges must be an even number as a range is represented as a pair of start and end time of working hours. The ranges will be empty if the event date is a non-working day.
Struct.name: EventDateRanges
